This paper deals with the problem of secure communication over a Gaussian MIMO broadcast channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses practical aspects of the problem, such as multiple antennas and channel characteristics, which fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
